<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="345" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-24"><hi rend="italic">November 24,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Minister from Nicaragua is advised by his Government that British minister to
                        Nicaragua declares England does not accept Nicaraguan rule in Mosquito
                        territory, and that British minister has telegraphed to Limon for English
                        war vessel to go to Bluefields. While this information is not fully credited
                        here, you will inquire and report.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>